      {
         "id": "SECTION_rules",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Rules\n\nThe main objective of this game is to reinforce the idea that even when we perform additions with large or consecutive numbers, we always add two numbers at a time.\n\nTo play, use the side arrows (<i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size: 1.5em\" name=\"traineeUp\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size: 1.5em\" name=\"traineeDown\"></i>) to perform the additions; however, we suggest trying to calculate them first.\n\nWith each correct result, the operation will shift to the side, and a part of an archaeological site or museum will be displayed.\n\nUpon completion, you will receive a medal (<i class=\"fa-solid fa-medal\" style=\"color:gold;\"></i>) and can perform a new calculation by clicking the corresponding button (<i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right\"></i>).",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
